<br>
OK, on to class. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START 8) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/glasses.gif ALT="8)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
From level 1-4, you're the other melee classes, except that you can buff yourself (Chant of Battle) and dish out DoT damage (Chords of Dissonance).  You also become the best friend of anyone with a lost corpse at level 4 when you get Locating Lyric, the corpse-finding song.  FWIW, buy CoB and Chords as soon as you can; you can lay off Jig'o'Vigor a bit if you need gear, but do get it soon so you can practice twisting songs.  (More on twisting later.)<br>
<br>
At level 5 you get one of our class-defining songs - Selo's Accelerando.  Get this song as soon as you can, and a drum as well.  Even at level 5, you'll be + 36% to running speed with your drum, and without a drum you'll still be able to outrun most monsters you're fighting.  More about Selo's and SoW later.<br>
<br>
Now for the scary part - almost all of our instruments are two-handed and equip in the secondary melee slot.  Yes, you have no weapons or shields... but if you're travelling cross-country at this point you are better off running rather than fighting anyway.  The key is that the appropriate instrument increases the song effect, and that's usually desirable.  (Note that some songs are voice-only.)  Right-click and hold on the song gem to see what instrument (percussion, strings, wind, brass or voice) works with the song in question.  A few songs REQUIRE an instrument to be equipped to function (Sonorous Clouding, our level 19 invisibilty song, requires wind instruments to be equipped.)<br>
<br>
This brings me to another tip - as part of your spare gear in the bank, put at least one complete set of whatever instruments you can use away for CR.  You may want more than one spare drum (you WILL get hooked on Selo's, trust me).  At 19th, make sure you have a spare wind instrument in case you need invisibility to recover your body.  Spare strings can be useful for lulling (Lugubrious lament, level <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START 8) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/glasses.gif ALT="8)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  or healing (Hymn of Restoration, 6th level) if it's a long and perilous run.  Brass is less crucial, at least to my level (27th) but I keep one just in case.<br>
<br>
Next, your hotkeys and twisting.  You will find yourself setting up several banks of these fairly early.  I'll discuss the different banks I have later, but for now let's focus on bank 1, my primary.<br>
<br>
In the first six slots, I have the songs I expect to need the most, or to need in a hurry.  1, 2 and 3 are the main songs I expect to twist during a fight.  Slot 4 for me is traditionally Selo's; if indoors I'll usually put Jig'o'Vigor in there.  5 and 6 are songs I expect to need quickly, such as Lullaby (mezz) or Guardian Rhythms (if we pull a caster).  Songs for downtime (Chant of Clarity, Hymn) don't need a hotkey.  You can also access songs which aren't hotkeys by holding down ALT and pressing the number you want ( 1-8 ).<br>
<br>
Slots 7 and 8 are primary and secondary melee, with 9 &amp; 10 being general inventory slots 1 and 2.  This allows me to change from weapons to instruments, or if instrument fighting to swap instruments.  You can't use these as keys, but it saves time compared to switching to inventory screen during a fight.<br>
<br>
Twisting 101 now.  It's simple, really. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START 8) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/glasses.gif ALT="8)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   You can start twisting as low as level 2, if you are careful about where you are. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   Let's assume you're a third level bard twisting your three songs someplace away from NPCs or guards, and your songs are in slots 1, 2 and 3 of your hotkey bank.<br>
<br>
Start singing Chant of Battle by pressing 1.  When you see the &quot;Your pulse quickens&quot; message, press 1 again, then press 2.  When you see &quot;A (whatever) winces&quot;, press 2 again, then press 3.  When you see the effect message for Jig, press 3 again, then 1.  It will look something like this:<br>
1,12,23,31,12,23,31......<br>
<br>
Practice this!  Any decent bard should be able to twist 3 songs at once, and I'll tell you how to squeeze in 4 or 5 later.<br>
<br>
