<br>
If the songs you're twisting are in slots 1, 2 and 3 and you have 1,2 and 3 hoteyed to those songs you can now twist like so...<br>
<br>
1... wait for effect...<br>
2, song stops, 2... wait for second effect...<br>
3, song stops, 3... wait for third effect...<br>
1, song stops, 1... wait for first effect...<br>
<br>
Etc. In other words you can press any song hotkey to stop the current song, so when I'm twisting for a little easier management of what I'm thinking and doing I just double hit the song I want like hitting 1 1 really fast will stop whatever song is playing and start song 1. 2 2 will stop whatever's playing and start song 2, etc.<br>
<br>
Just a different way to accomplish the same thing, I just find it easier to do it that way so I can sit a finger on the key I *want* to be playing. <p><hr align="center" width="80%" size="2">
